Seventh Term = a + 6d
Seventh Term = \frac{42}{45} + 6(\frac{-1}{45})
Seventh Term = \frac{42-6}{45}
Seven Term = \frac{36}{45}
Lastly, simplify 36 over 45 by dividing both the numerator and the denominator by 9
36 / 9 = 4   so the numerator becomes 4, and 45/9 becomes 5.
The seventh term simplifies to \frac{4}{5}.

